Spellglyph	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.GeometerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A spellglyph is an arcane diagram that substitutes for a specifi c spell's verbal and material components (if any). When a geometer casts a prepared spell in conjunction with a spellglyph scribed for that spell, he can cast the spell as if it were affected by the Silent Spell feat. The spellglyph replaces any material components (other than a focus) normally required by the spell. A geometer chooses at the time of casting whether to use a spellglyph. An expended spellglyph disappears, just like any other material component. Spellglyphs are normally scribed on parchment, much like scrolls. Preparing a spellglyph requires 1 hour and the use of rare inks costing 25 gp per spell level. If the spell normally requires an expensive material component (with a value of more than 1 gp), exotic inks and treatments of equal cost must be used in the preparation of the spellglyph.	KEY:Geometer ~ Spellglyph																										SORTKEY:Class_Geometer	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
Book of Geometry	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.GeometerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:At 2nd level and higher, a geometer uses a unique system for recording the details of a spell that drastically reduces the expense of maintaining spellbooks. Every spell he learns from now on requires only a single page in his spellbook. It still takes 24 hours to scribe a spell into a spellbook and materials costing 100 gp per page. A geometer's spellbook is diffi cult for nongeometers to decipher and use. The Spellcraft DC to decipher or prepare spells from a geometer's spellbook is increased by 5 for nongeometers (see page 178 of the Player's Handbook).	KEY:Geometer ~ Book of Geometry	/																	AUTO:EQUIP|Book of Geometry								SORTKEY:Class_Geometer	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
Sigilsight	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.GeometerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A geometer of 3rd level or higher can use a Search check to find magic traps based on runes, glyphs, sigils, symbols, and other writings as a rogue can. He gains a bonus equal to his caster level on all Search checks to find traps of this sort. A geometer who merely comes within 10 feet of a magic rune, glyph, sigil, or symbol, or the threshold of danger for such a device, is entitled to make a Search check as if he were actively searching for a magic trap.	KEY:Geometer ~ Sigilsight																										SORTKEY:Class_Geometer	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
Pass Sigil	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.GeometerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Supernatural	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Beginning at 3rd level, a geometer can temporarily negate magical wards based on written symbols, sigils, runes, or glyphs. As a standard action, a geometer can attempt to pass such a sigil. He must succeed on a level check (DC 6 + the sigil creator's caster level). If successful, he can suppress the effects of the device for as long as he maintains concentration (which might make it possible for others to pass the sigil safely, too). A geometer must be able to see the device to be passed.	KEY:Geometer ~ Pass Sigil																										SORTKEY:Class_Geometer	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
Powerful Spellglyph	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.GeometerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When a 5th-level geometer prepares a spellglyph for a spell, he knows how to strengthen the spell beyond its normal effects. His caster level is treated as 1 higher for any spell he casts with the use of a spellglyph.	KEY:Geometer ~ Powerful Spellglyph																										SORTKEY:Class_Geometer	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
Greater Glyph of Warding	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.GeometerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A 5th-level geometer adds greater glyph of warding to his spellbook as a 6th-level arcane spell. He can prepare and cast the spell just like any other spell he knows.	KEY:Geometer ~ Greater Glyph of Warding									BONUS:SPELLKNOWN|TYPE=Arcane;LEVEL=6|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Geometer	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
