Spells per Day	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:At each level, an Initiate of the Sevenfold Veil gains new spells per day (and spells known, if applicable) as if she had also gained a level in an arcane spellcasting class to which she belonged before adding the prestige class level. She does not, however, gain any other benefi t a character of that class would have gained (such as the bonus feat sometimes gained by a wizard). If she had more than one arcane spellcasting class before becoming an Initiate of the Sevenfold Veil, she must decide to which class to add each level for the purpose of determining spells per day and spells known.	KEY:Initiate of the Seven Veil ~ Spells per Day																										SORTKEY:Class_Initiate_Of_The_Sevenfold_Veil	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
Warding	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.SpellLike	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:An Initiate of the Sevenfold Veil can create a warding. She can choose one veil she knows (see below) to be imbued in the warding. A warding lasts for a certain amount of time as indicated in its description, unless it is dismissed (the same way a spell is dismissed; see page 176 of the Player's Handbook). When she creates a warding, she can choose one of three types.	KEY:Initiate of the Seven Veil ~ Warding	DESC:%1/day.|WardingTimes			DEFINE:WardingTimes|0					BONUS:VAR|WardingTimes|(InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilLVL+1)/2																	SORTKEY:Class_Initiate_Of_The_Sevenfold_Veil	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
Veil	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.SpellLike	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When an initiate creates a warding, she can choose and imbue the warding with any one veil she knows how to create. These veils duplicate the layers of a prismatic wall and are described below. An initiate's caster level for these veils is equal to her arcane spellcaster level.	KEY:Initiate of the Seven Veil ~ Veil																		ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Initiate of the Sevenfold Veil ~ Veil ~ Red Veil|PREVARGTEQ:InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilLVL,1	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Initiate of the Sevenfold Veil ~ Veil ~ Orange Veil|PREVARGTEQ:InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilLVL,2	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Initiate of the Sevenfold Veil ~ Veil ~ Yellow Veil|PREVARGTEQ:InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilLVL,3	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Initiate of the Sevenfold Veil ~ Veil ~ Green Veil|PREVARGTEQ:InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilLVL,4	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Initiate of the Sevenfold Veil ~ Veil ~ Blue Veil|PREVARGTEQ:InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilLVL,5	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Initiate of the Sevenfold Veil ~ Veil ~ Indigo Veil|PREVARGTEQ:InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilLVL,6	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Initiate of the Sevenfold Veil ~ Veil ~ Violet Veil|PREVARGTEQ:InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilLVL,7		SORTKEY:Class_Initiate_Of_The_Sevenfold_Veil	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
Red Veil	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The fi rst veil an initiate learns is the red veil. A warding imbued with this veil blocks all nonmagical ranged attacks and missiles. A creature crossing a red veil takes 20 points of fi re damage (Refl ex half). A cone of cold spell or effect destroys a warding with this veil but is negated in the process. A warding with this veil is the equivalent of a 4th-level spell.	KEY:Initiate of the Seven Veil ~ Veil ~ Red Veil																										SORTKEY:Class_Initiate_Of_The_Sevenfold_Veil	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
Orange Veil	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:At 2nd level, an initiate learns the secret of the orange veil. A warding with this veil halts magical ranged attacks, including spells that conjure missiles (such as Melf's acid arrow) or create rays (such as disintegrate or a beholder's eye rays) but not spells that do not require a ranged attack (such as magic missile). A creature crossing an orange veil takes 40 points of acid damage (Refl ex half). A gust of wind spell or similar effect destroys the veil but is negated in the process. A warding with this veil is the equivalent of a 5th-level spell.	KEY:Initiate of the Seven Veil ~ Veil ~ Orange Veil																										SORTKEY:Class_Initiate_Of_The_Sevenfold_Veil	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
Yellow Veil	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:An initiate of 3rd level or higher can create a yellow veil. This veil prevents gases or clouds from entering the warded area, and it defeats petrifi cation attacks. In addition, a character inside a personal or area warding imbued with a yellow veil has immunity to poison introduced from outside the warding (such as from a creature with an envenomed weapon striking through the barrier). A creature crossing a yellow veil takes 80 points of electricity damage (Refl ex half). A disintegrate spell destroys theveil but is negated in the process. A warding with this veil is the equivalent of a 6th-level spell.	KEY:Initiate of the Seven Veil ~ Veil ~ Yellow Veil																										SORTKEY:Class_Initiate_Of_The_Sevenfold_Veil	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
Green Veil	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A 4th-level initiate masters the green veil. This veil stops the passage of breath weapons. A creature crossing a green veil must succeed on a Fortitude save or die; on a successful save, the creature takes 1d6 points of Constitution damage. This veil is a poison effect. A passwall spell destroys a green veil. A warding with this veil is the equivalent of a 6th-level spell.	KEY:Initiate of the Seven Veil ~ Veil ~ Green Veil																										SORTKEY:Class_Initiate_Of_The_Sevenfold_Veil	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
Indigo Veil	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A 6th-level initiate can create the mighty indigo veil. This veil prevents the passage of all spells or spell-like abilities. Any creature crossing an indigo veil must succeed on a Will save or become confused, as if by an insanity spell. A daylight spell negates and is negated by an indigo veil. A warding with this veil is the equivalent of a 7th-level spell.	KEY:Initiate of the Seven Veil ~ Veil ~ Indigo Veil																										SORTKEY:Class_Initiate_Of_The_Sevenfold_Veil	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
Violet Veil	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:At 7th level, an initiate masters the seventh and fi nal veil: the violet veil. This barrier destroys all objects and effects that cross it, as if they were disintegrated. Living creatures passing a violet veil must succeed on a Will save or be shifted to a random place on a random plane (as the plane shift spell). A violet veil is destroyed by a successful dispel magic spell. A warding with this veil is the equivalent of an 8th-level spell.	KEY:Initiate of the Seven Veil ~ Veil ~ Violet Veil																										SORTKEY:Class_Initiate_Of_The_Sevenfold_Veil	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
Unimpeachable Abjuration	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:An initiate's abjuration spells are particularly diffi cult to defeat with spells or effects that dispel them. An initiate can add her class level to the DC to dispel any abjuration spell or effect she creates.	KEY:Initiate of the Seven Veil ~ Unimpeachable Abjuration									BONUS:DC|SCHOOL.Anjuration|InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilLVL																	SORTKEY:Class_Initiate_Of_The_Sevenfold_Veil	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
Unanswerable Strike	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Due to her study of magical defenses, an initiate learns how to defeat them more easily. At 2nd level and higher, she gains a +2 bonus on caster level checks to counter or dispel abjuration spells. At 6th level, this bonus increases to a +4 bonus.	KEY:Initiate of the Seven Veil ~ Unanswerable Strike																										SORTKEY:Class_Initiate_Of_The_Sevenfold_Veil	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
Reactive Warding	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.SpellLike	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:At 4th level, an initiate learns to create a warding (see above) in response to an attack. She can raise a warding as an immediate action (see page 86), after an opponent begins an action but before it is completed. For example, if she sees an enemy warrior charging her, she can raise a warding to protect herself. The opponent can choose to continue the charge through the warding or can halt outside it.	KEY:Initiate of the Seven Veil ~ Reactive Warding																										SORTKEY:Class_Initiate_Of_The_Sevenfold_Veil	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
Double Warding	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilClassFeatures.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:At 6th level and higher, an initiate can raise two veils at once any time she creates a warding. This still counts as only one use of her warding ability. The less powerful effect (progressing from red up through violet) is always considered to be "outside" the more powerful effect, so a double warding consisting of a blue veil and a green veil would subject any creature passing through to the green veil fi rst, followed by the blue veil. To negate the entire warding, the outermost veil must be negated before the inner veil can be negated.	KEY:Initiate of the Seven Veil ~ Double Warding																										SORTKEY:Class_Initiate_Of_The_Sevenfold_Veil	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
Kaleidoscopi Doom	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.InitiateOfTheSevenfoldVeilClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.SpellLike	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:At 7th level, an Initiate of the Sevenfold Veil learns the secret of the awesome kaleidoscopic doom. Once per day as a standard action, she designates one creature within 60 feet and turns magical effects currently affecting the creature against it. This effect functions like a targeted greater dispel magic, except that for every spell or effect negated on the target, the effect of one veil (see above) is visited on the victim as if the subject had crossed it. The veils created around the victim proceed through the spectrum from red to violet, with one veil activated per spell negated. Thus, a creature with three spells negated would be subject to the effects of the red, orange, and yellow veils. The subject is still entitled to the normal saving throws allowed by each veil. This ability is the equivalent of a 9thlevel spell.	KEY:Initiate of the Seven Veil ~ Kaleidoscopic Doom																										SORTKEY:Class_Initiate_Of_The_Sevenfold_Veil	SOURCEPAGE:CA	
